def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index

    clocs = [index._get_level_number(i) if i in index.names else index.names.index(i) for i in clocs]

    r_locs = [idx for idx in range(index.nlevels) if idx not in clocs]
    r_indices = [index.levels[i] for i in r_locs]
    r_levels = [index.codes[i] for i in r_locs]
    r_names = [index.names[i] for i in r_locs]

    group_index = get_group_index(r_levels, sort=False, xnull=False)
    comp_ids, obs_ids = compress_group_index(group_index, sort=False)
    recons_codes = decons_obs_group_ids(comp_ids, obs_ids, r_levels, xnull=False)

    dummy_index = MultiIndex(levels=r_indices + [obs_ids], codes=r_levels + [comp_ids], names=r_names + ["__placeholder__"], verify_integrity=False)
    dummy = data.copy()
    dummy.index = dummy_index

    unstacked = dummy.unstack("__placeholder__", fill_value=fill_value)
    new_levels = index.levels[clocs]
    new_names = index.names[clocs]
    new_codes = recons_codes

    new_columns = MultiIndex(levels=[unstacked.index.levels[0]] + new_levels, codes=[unstacked.index.codes[0]] + new_codes, names=[data.columns.name] + new_names, verify_integrity=False)

    if isinstance(unstacked, Series):
        unstacked.index = new_columns
    else:
        unstacked.columns = new_columns

    return unstacked
